public interface CommandDescriptor
This interface defines a descriptor of a command. A descriptor should provide a name of the command, a full name for display purpose, and a help message. The command name should be unique and contain no space. The help message should be in a wiki format. See Wiki for more details. It is recommended to include the name, the short description, the full description, the synopses, the argument descriptions, and the examples in the help message but this is not required.
Author:
"Ming-Hsien Tsai"
